<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-341-026  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 341 026.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  June 12 1989 v6 n23 p28(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>LAN Services software to provide integrated financial modeling.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   LAN Services Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   BUYout! (Computer program) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software packagesFinancial SoftwareProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>LAN Services Inc. is readying new Windows-based software designed to helpfinancial professionals perform analyses for company valuations and leveragedbuyouts.andM;BUYout! was developed on Microsoft Corp.'s Excel spreadsheet using programmacros and C routines, according to officials in the company's FinancialSystems Group in New York.andM;The program offers financial models for analyzing and forecasting cash flow,income statements, capitalization, tax schedules, cost of goods and otherbusiness-performance indicators.andM;Integrity CheckerandM;Unlike simpler spreadsheet add-in or template packages, however, BUYout! isan integrated financial-modeling system that checks data integrity, accordingto company officials.andM;For example, the model ensures that forecasted balance sheets are correctlylinked to forecasted income statements and cash-flow reports.andM;BUYout! runs under Microsoft Windows on IBM and compatible micros, andrequires 2M bytes of memory and Excel 2.1 or higher.andM;Pricing for the program, scheduled for release by the end of the month, hasnot yet been set.andM;LAN Services' Financial Systems Group can be reached at (212) 797-3800.andO;</TEXT></DOC>